FT  28 OCT 93 / Fuel VAT at 8% 'will raise Pounds 930m'
VALUE ADDED TAX on domestic fuel bills at 8 per cent would raise an
estimated Pounds 930m in 1994-95, the first year planned for the new tax,
said Sir John Cope, the paymaster general, last night. He said in a Commons
written reply that the revenue would be Pounds 2.85bn in 1996-97, when the
rate would be 17.5 per cent.
